{"abstract":[{"text":"VoiceOver provides spoken descriptions and braille output of onscreen elements. Learn how to go beyond the visuals to identify VoiceOver and functional issues to help improve the experience for all users.","type":"text"}],"kind":"article","schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc18-226-voiceover-app-testing-beyond-the-visuals"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Be the hero to change that by reading the transcript and providing notes! It’s super easy:","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing"}]},{"anchor":"Related-Sessions","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Related Sessions"},{"style":"list","type":"links","items":["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10019-App-accessibility-for-Switch-Control","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18-230-Deliver-an-Exceptional-Accessibility-Experience","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-806-Design-For-Everyone"]}],"kind":"content"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18-226-VoiceOver-App-Testing-Beyond-The-Visuals"},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"title":"VoiceOver: App Testing Beyond The Visuals","roleHeading":"WWDC18","role":"sampleCode"},"sampleCodeDownload":{"action":{"isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"Read Transcript","identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2018\/226\/","type":"reference"},"kind":"sampleDownload"},"sections":[],"references":{"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC18":{"kind":"article","type":"topic","images":[{"identifier":"WWDC18-Icon.png","type":"icon"},{"identifier":"WWDC18.jpeg","type":"card"}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc18","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18","role":"collectionGroup","title":"WWDC18","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Xcode 10, Swift 4.2, iOS 12, macOS 10.14 (Mojave), tvOS 12, watchOS 5."}]},"WWDC18-Icon.png":{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC18-Icon.png","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18-Icon.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"alt":null},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC17-806-Design-For-Everyone":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17-806-design-for-everyone","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-806-Design-For-Everyone","abstract":[{"text":"By understanding the range of abilities and capabilities of the people who use our apps, you can design robust apps that work for everyone. Learn how designing for accessibility and inclusiveness can do social good, widen participation, and enable everyone to benefit.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","title":"Design For Everyone","role":"sampleCode","kind":"article"},"WWDC18.jpeg":{"identifier":"WWDC18.jpeg","type":"image","alt":null,"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18.jpeg","traits":["1x","light"]}]},"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn More…"}],"url":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","title":"Learn More…"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC18-230-Deliver-an-Exceptional-Accessibility-Experience":{"type":"topic","role":"sampleCode","abstract":[{"text":"Go beyond the basics and create apps with an exceptional accessibility experience. Learn how to design elements that appear in your app for